        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 10:46PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 1044 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Madisonville, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Heavy Rain capable of causing minor flooding in low-
lying and poor drainage locations; pea size hail.

SOURCE...Heavy rain of over 1.5 inches per hour has been
reported by spotters. Hail potential is radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor flooding of low-lying and poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Madisonville, Trinity, and Lovelady.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
